{"add":{"doc":{"id":"0f74d8145ac7c2d0a5f87a497c65fc83a695db5426e25c556df1012a3cabd283","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/Symian_virus.png/220px-Symian_virus.png","previous":[],"after":["Viruses are small infectious agents that can replicate only inside the living cells of an organism. Viruses infect all forms of life, including animals, plants, fungi, bacteria and archaea. They are found in almost every ecosystem on Earth and are the most abundant type of biological entity, with millions of different types, although only about 5,000 viruses have been described in detail. Some viruses cause disease in humans, and others are responsible for economically important diseases of livestock and crops."]}}}